This paper proposes a new model for knowledge graph embedding, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is based on bilinear diagonal models, which are commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing (cs.LG, cs.CL). The paper also focuses on answering path queries in knowledge graphs, which is a common task in database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of fast computation techniques, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
